The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 January is 166,153 (19,150.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 January, there were 11,178 new confirmed cases (1,288.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 December, there were 11,912 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 6% (734 fewer cases).
